There will be a time when you want to force some configuration data of the extension and plugin to be specific to your custom shield. Here is an example on how to set the [comment captcha][link:../reference/extension/plugin/comment-captcha] type to `text` with black background and blue color using a hook:

~~~ .php
Hook::set('plugin.state.comment-captcha', function($lot) {
    $lot['type'] = 'text';
    $lot['types']['text'][0] = '000';
    $lot['types']['text'][1] = '00f';
    return $lot;
});
~~~

Example for [extension][link:../reference/extension]:

~~~ .php
Hook::set('extend.state.minify', function($lot) { … });
~~~

Example for [shield][link:../reference/shield]:

~~~ .php
Hook::set('shield.state.document', function($lot) { … });
~~~